Kutiva eLearning platform
=========================

This is kutiva elearning platform for students.

Local Development
-----------------

### Development

    # Get this repo (you must clone with `--recursive`)
    git clone --recursive https://github.com/h3zTr0n/kutiva.git

    # Change to this repo's directory.
    cd kutiva

    # install python3.6 on your machine go http//:python.org
    # install pip
    `sudo apt-get install python3.6-pip`
    # In cmd or terminal install virtualenv run pip install virtualenv
    # create vritualenv and activate into the invironment
    `virtualenv venv --python=/usr/bin/python3.6`
    # activate into the virtualenvironment
    `source venv/bin/activate`
    # run
    `pip install -r requirements.txt`
    # then to create migrations run
    `manage.py makemigrations`
    # run
    `python manage.py migrate to create the db tables`

    # Create your initial user.
    python manage.py createsuperuser

    # Start debug server.
    python manage.py runserver

    # Visit the website in your browser at http://127.0.0.1:8000

    # Enjoy
